channel.title: Help me
channel.description:
Hello everyone. I need a lil bit of help.
First it used to work then idk what happend.
But i cant get on any server at all like making my own wise. Everytime i load my client and run. It works. And i changed the ip on the client to mine. And i have a no-ip set up. And i think..my environmental varibles are set up correctly they was before. And when i go to connect on a 317. It just says error connecting to server and when i try to do it on a 508 the loading red bar just stays and doesnt go up. Anyone help?

item.title: Help me
item.dc:creator: @deathschaos9 DeathsChaos9
item.description:
@deathschaos9 wrote:

You can never you your no-ip to log into your own server, unless it is hosted on a VPS, the hoster always has to use localhost.

item.title: Help me
item.dc:creator: @deathschaos9 DeathsChaos9
item.description:
@deathschaos9 wrote:

[quote=“SirPali, post:2, topic:327501”]Sounds like a portforwarding problem.
Check if your portforwarding is alright, or try a localhost client and see if that works.[/quote]

Try again, a portforwarding problem would mean other people cant log in, he said he cant log in.

[quote=“cbk666, post:1, topic:327501”]Hello everyone. I need a lil bit of help.

First it used to work then idk what happend.

But i cant get on any server at all like making my own wise. Everytime i load my client and run. It works. And i changed the ip on the client to mine. And i have a no-ip set up. And i think…my environmental varibles are set up correctly they was before. And when i go to connect on a 317. It just says error connecting to server and when i try to do it on a 508 the loading red bar just stays and doesnt go up. Anyone help?[/quote]

Make sure the server ip is set to localhost or you wont be able to log in.
